Program: Discovery
Title: Discovering cortisone
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxg9
Last Broadcast Date: 03 August 1999
The discovery of cortisone by Philip Showalter Hench. While a researcher at the Mayo Clinic Showalter Hench found the cure for arthritis by using the natural hormone cortisol and the use of steriods which mimic its effects.